reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got this to mount a couple of 24 inch monitors to the wall in my daughters room over a small desk tucked in a corner with a mid size dell computer. To mount I needed to hang the monitors directly to the sheet rock which is never my first choice. The mounts are very light weight and minimalist designs but do the job well. There was no issues with the vesa connection to the monitors. I did not use the mounting hardware that came with the mount. Instead I purchased some much larger sheetrock screw inserts that I could screw the wall side of the mount to. ( I got CONFAST 50 Pack Nylon Self-Drilling Drywall/Hollow-Wall Anchor Kit with Screws, (25 Anchors+25 Screws) Includes #8 Anchors with Screws ) off amazon here when I ordered the mounts for about 7 dollars) The confast mounts worked brilliantly and gave a very stable mount. Once wall and vesa side mounts wire installed it was easy to push monitor against wall and slide it down so the computer side slid into the wall part of the mount. There is a bit of side to side play in the mounts that allows the monitors go off level a tiny bit but its easy to just touch it and re-level it. The attachment to the wall is so close that trying to get to mount to stabilize that just isn't going to happen. I consider that a bonus for how close to the wall they are. The desk is very narrow that my daughter is using so the the distance between her and wall is not very far. A mount that pushed the monitors forward would put them to close to her. The monitors were different brands/models so the vesa mounts were at different heights to line the monitors up at the same eye level. One of those things though that you just have to figure out on your own.Over all they were an extremely cheap and effective solution for our needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Basic mount no adjustment
reviews.reviewText: The picture is a representation of the bracket. However the enlarged aspect masks the gauge of the sheet metal. I wouldn't call it "heavy duty construction" but it is adequate. It is a basic mount with no adjustment. Due to the design the monitor will have a very slight downward tilt. This can be corrected by installing washers between the monitor and bracket on the bottom screws. Definitely low profile but you do sacrifice adjustability. As for the "14 to 24 inches..." I wouldn't have a problem with a larger monitor as long as it does not exceed the 30lb capacity but I personally would not use this bracket in any moving vehicle. I will be buying more.My specific install depicted in the attached pictures...I needed an even greater tilt due to my mounting position. This was achieved with spacers (nuts) on the top screws as pictured. Just wanted to note that I used the screws that came with the monitor not the bracket. The screws supplied were not long enough to accommodate the spacers I used.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not heavy duty, but the price is right if you don't need the strength.
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for something low profile for the camper. The bracket is only 18 GA steel, so I wouldn't trust anything close to what is advertised (30 lbs?). I honestly wouldn't put more than 10 lbs on it. Based on the picture, I expected 12 GA steel, or maybe 14 GA. It is worth the price, but no more than that.

reviews.reviewText: At first the tiny size scared me, but after the install I was totally pleased with the robust and simplistic design. Its easy to remove and replace TV to add or remove cables. The brackets sit real close to the wall, so I had to purchase right angle HDMI and cable adapters to make it work with my TV as the connections are on the back of the TV and not the side. Other than that, PERFECT!

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I had two order one of the was prefect,but second one was missing screw pack(Wall anchor$).I had to use my own screws from my tool box,but the installation was easy and I liked the simplicity of hanging it so I did not return it.I have ordered two more,but please be careful about parts/screws when you send it for future.

Too much distance between the two parts to be assembled, which consequently causes excessive vertical inclination, and a less marked horizontal oscillation. I recommend using different rubber spacers between the upper and lower parts, in order to at least compensate for the excessive vertical inclination.
